---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Integrations"
  description="CodeArmy is designed to connect Trae Solo, CLI automation, collaboration surfaces, and remote execution workflows."
>
  <section class="container page-hero">
    <p class="eyebrow">Integrations</p>
    <h1>Use the same campaign state across multiple entry points.</h1>
    <p class="lead">
      CodeArmy should not be locked to a single chat surface. The product is strongest when the
      same campaign can be entered from Trae Solo, scripts, collaboration tools, and remote
      execution environments.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="container page-body grid-2">
    <article class="card">
      <h3>Trae Solo</h3>
      <p>
        The primary entry point for daily use. CodeArmy should appear as custom agents, Skills, and
        MCP tools behind SOLO Coder.
      </p>
    </article>
    <article class="card">
      <h3>CLI</h3>
      <p>
        The automation-friendly surface for initializing campaigns, reconciling state, and building
        reports in scripts or scheduled jobs.
      </p>
    </article>
    <article class="card">
      <h3>Feishu</h3>
      <p>
        A collaboration surface for summaries, approvals, and outbound notifications. Useful, but
        not the product center of gravity.
      </p>
    </article>
    <article class="card">
      <h3>Cluster / HPC</h3>
      <p>
        The execution surface where research experiments actually run. CodeArmy is most valuable
        when campaign state stays connected to remote jobs and metric outputs.
      </p>
    </article>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
